<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1144">
A company has $n$ employees with certain salaries. Your task is to keep track of the salaries and process queries.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line contains two integers $n$ and $q$: the number of employees and queries. The employees are numbered $1,2,\ldots,n$.<br />
<br />
The next line has $n$ integers $p_1,p_2,\ldots,p_n$: each employee's salary.<br />
<br />
After this, there are $q$ lines describing the queries. Each line has one of the following forms:<ul>
<li><code>!</code> $k$ $x$: change the salary of employee $k$ to $x$<br />
<li><code>?</code> $a$ $b$: count the number of employees whose salary is between $a \ldots b$<br />
</ul>
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the answer to each <code>?</code> query.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n, q \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le p_i \le 10^9$<br />
<li>$1 \le k \le n$<br />
<li>$1 \le x \le 10^9$<br />
<li>$1 \le a \le b \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5 3<br />
3 7 2 2 5<br />
? 2 3<br />
! 3 6<br />
? 2 3</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>3<br />
2</code>    </div>
